0198231,0.02489051,-0.01363540,0.03658948,-0.00702114,0.06900467,-0.01161789,0.06747807,-0.02722361,-0.01399903,0.03099115,0.03566274,-0.03652378,-0.01006304,-0.06223596,0.01655904,0.01696146,-0.01082972,-0.03622837,-0.01419102,-0.05756097,-0.00808842,0.09280076,-0.03032593,-0.01095370,-0.05086487,0.05318399,-0.01637366,-0.02074902,-0.03869370,0.02222984,-0.06542882,0.01057408,0.05773417,-0.05260915,0.01016564,-0.01891519,0.02931794,0.08181572,0.02528323,0.04344098,-0.02081710,-0.01990152]',E'Centralized Version Control Systems\n\nIf the hard disk the central database is on becomes corrupted, and proper backups haven''t been kept, you lose absolutely everything -- the entire history of the project except whatever single snapshots people happen to have on their local machines.\nLocal VCSs suffer from this same problem -- whenever you have the entire history of the project in a single place, you risk losing everything.','{"source": "git", "version": "2", "language": "bash", "title": "About Version Control.Asc", "section_title": "about-version-control.asc", "url": "https://github.com/progit/progit2/blob/main/book/01-introduction/sections/about-version-control.asc", "topics": "git,vcs,branching,about,version,control.asc", "categories": "devops,vcs,scm"}');
